reviews.review_text:
Must be a recent post It's hard to believe noone has commented on this yet.  God Bless the chain of events that lead to this recording to my ears!!!  Supposedly an "Audience" recording (wink-wink, nudge-nudge).  Beauty-Aye?  A thousand thank-you'z!!!
Wg

I'll comment, yeah... I was at this concert.

I was 19 years old and it was my first Dead Show... some old drunk hippie selling tickets saw me standing in the rain... grumbles, "Ya wanna buy a ticket?!" Told him I had no money, that I had just hopped in the car for the heck of it.

He goes, "Here... keep these dry (crumpled up old pack of Winstons) ....here, I got a ticket for you, bruther."

"For free? You serious? You're going to give me a ticket?"

"I got a ticket for you, bruther, hold on (magically produces a $20 ticket from his pockets) ....THEY OUGHTA GIVE THE GOD DAMNED THINGS AWAY!!!!"

Off I went.

And there it is, as it was, as it shall be.
(That's like forever, yo.
You never forget things like this.)

How rare to find such a recording.
Thank you.

Sincerely.

Mud Bowl '89 '88 Alpine shows were called the Dust Bowl, and '89 Alpine shows were called the Mud Bowl. As I recall all 3 shows were cold and rainy and I witnessed an overdose...but man were those shows hot! Listening to them for the first time since '89. Great Memories.
Recording? This recording sounds good unless you are listening with a subwoofer, in which case, there's a lot of low-end rumble at various points throughout.
